The Escapists is a strategic game where the aim is to escape from a prison establishment in the middle of nowhere . I started playing a few weeks ago and I was actually having a lot of fun .However, when I finally got to the Jungle prison (4th prison) . I had been caught digging and whenever I pressed load last save it would send me to my cell and as soon as I left my cell I would be arrested for digging again . this happened over and over again and the only way to get out was to go to solitary.

The game is hard to understand without any outside help from the internet. The tutorial doesnt explain that guards have keys all it does is show ways of exiting the prison. This way beginners (such as myself) will waste lots of time trying to understand what to do. Some tools are not explained with information of what they do which causes confusion and the player to not be satisfied with the game and in game actions. Game has holy potential its a shame this happened and I wish for a change.

Now that I can actually play the game i can give a proper review now i think the gameplay is good, easy to learn how to play. I now give this game a 5 star because the game is running as smooth as silk (until I crash but that's on me) and I am glad I can now attempt to beat the later prison's on soon after I'm done with this game I shall move on to the second game! I expect great things from you game dev's

content: It is a good classic game about escaping prison with a little story

The on-screen controls are impossible to use because on small phone screens. The control surface area is far too small to actually be able to gain control over the way the character moves. Team17 does not offer refunds if the game doesn't work on your phone. Been two years, still no refund, despite answering their emails.
replyContent:
Good morning Mike, 

Our sincere apologies for the delay in responding to your emails.
Please see the reply that we recently sent that will hopefully assist us in resolving your issue.
Once we have the requested information, we will do our best to resolve the matter.

Kind Regards, 
Team17

WARNING THE FOLLOWING IS MY OPINION!   The Escapists is one my top 5 favourite games ever. So When I heard that it was on mobile I was super excited. I was surprised (in a good way) and a little disappointed. The thing that surprised me was how well they integrated it into mobile. It was done very well, and the controls are very smooth and easy to get used to, which was one of my fears when you guys announced that it was coming to mobile. The part that disappointed me was that they chose the Xbox look. I kinda dislike the Xbox version because it changes everything (in terms of look/textures, and the music. BTW I do like the way you guys did a remix of the soundtrack, that was very well done. But it would be nice to have an option in the game menu that changes the soundtrack from the remix version to the original version). I have always liked the PC version's simplistic looks and music, and this version (mobile and Xbox) changed that. So to recap this is still the game I love, now on mobile. But I wish they kept the PC textures and music, or at least an option to choose either one.   P.S developers, is this the finished product? Because so far what I've seen is that multitools (the most important tool in the game) and electronic screwdrivers are not able to be crafted.

This is a great game. The graphics, the gameplay, the soundtrack, the AI. Everything is perfect. However,  I have played the Xbox and PC version and I noticed some unusual behaviour with the mobile version. All inmates on Center Perks had no weapon, or a reasonably good weapon as I spawned.  I punched one of the inmates at morning rollcall to find that the guards hit them and not me. I then went on to steal their nunchuks (again in front of guards) and the guards didn't do a thing about it. At breakfast,  the guards just watched as I beat up fellow guards and when it was lockdown, I could easily throw a riot as all the guards were bunched up in a corner. Then, I escaped at 10:03 (world record?). The guard system for both Center Perks and Stalag Flucht make it extremely easy to escape on the first day. Overall, however,  this game is brilliant and I can't wait for the sequel.

content: I love  time

This game is time consuming when you have nothing to do but also doesn't drag on. It's not repeative at all. There's multiple ways to escape which makes it very interesting. The crafting system is not too complex but also not too simple. Every game mechanic of this game is well balanced. Overall it's just fun to play and worth the money. ^~^   The only problem with the game is when you are on lockdown and knock out a officer and take his key to try and escape, when the officer wakes it will send you to solitary confinement for stealing to key in the middle of you trying to excape. It's annoying but you can get around that problem if you have enough plastic keys (of the color you need). But that also makes it kinda pointless to try break out during a lockdown.   Also to the developers, could you possibly make a female prison? Overall I still love the game tho :)
Awesome

content: Great Game!!

This game is amazing, entertaining, and easy to get used to. The controls are easy to get the hang of early on, and the gameplay is difficult, but not to the point that it's too hard. All in all, it's a wonderful game. I just have a few suggestions such as if you're going to add the dlc and such that's on PC to the mobile version, and if we could rename the warden (I saw another person ask this and I think it's a brilliant idea). Also on some maps the guards are always around the cells during free period and it's too difficult to get items from other people's desks. On other maps, (including ones that are on a harder level than these ones) the guards aren't like this, and it's much easier to get items this way. I don't know if it's more of a perk from that prison, or if it's something others are experiencing, but I find it a bit annoying. Thank you for making this game, it's truly lovely and worth the buy.

I love the pixel Graphics they're great and the controls are pretty good too but when you try to hit someone and you didn't mean to your character follows them. But other than that the game is amazing I would recommend this game to anyone.
